---
description: Create signed commits when requested, never push automatically
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git commits

- When the user requests a commit, create it after reviewing the complete staged
  and unstaged diff and confirming no secrets are included.
- Create signed commits using the repository's configured Git identity.
- Never push, force-push, or otherwise update a remote unless the user
  explicitly requests it.
- If signing requires user interaction (such as a password or hardware-key
  confirmation), stop and ask the user to complete that interaction. Do not
  disable signing or bypass the configured signing mechanism.
